			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2023</a> paper:</span><br><i>Online Name-Based Navigation for Software Meta-languages</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/PeterDMosses.html">Peter D. Mosses</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1145/3623476.3623528">10.1145/3623476.3623528</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4a.html"><span class="tagM">T4A: Workbenches</span></a><ul><li> The paper provides tooling for precise name-based navigation of meta-language specifications in online repositories.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t3a.html"><span class="tagL">T3A: Meta-languages</span></a><ul><li> The target artefacts are specifications written in meta-languages used for language definition and implementation.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t5h.html"><span class="tagL">T5H: Usability</span></a><ul><li> The goal is to improve usability when browsing and understanding language specifications via web-based navigation.
</li></ul></li></ul>
